    "title": "Schema Design: PROJECTION_SCHEMA Enforces Tensor Output Structure",
    "content": "CYCLE 45 SCHEMA IMPLEMENTATION: PROJECTION_SCHEMA is a JSON schema (dict) that enforces the structure of Claude's tool-use response. COMPLETENESS: Defines all required fields: strands (array of objects), declared_losses (array), open_questions (array of strings), instructions_for_next (string), overall_truth/indeterminacy/falsity (numbers). STRAND DEFINITION: Each strand has: title (string, short label), content (string, integrated semantic content—NOT a summary, a projection), key_claims (array of claim objects). CLAIM DEFINITION: Each claim has: text (string, the assertion), truth (number, [0,1]), indeterminacy (number, [0,1]), falsity (number, [0,1]). NO SUM CONSTRAINT on T/I/F. Independent values. LOSS DEFINITION: Each loss has: what_was_lost (string, precise description of dropped content), why (string, justification), category (enum: context_pressure, traversal_bias, authorial_choice, practical_constraint). ENUM CATEGORIES: (1) context_pressure: Not enough tokens/space to include everything. (2) traversal_bias: Some information was de-prioritized in reasoning. (3) authorial_choice: Intentionally excluded (e.g., out of scope). (4) practical_constraint: External constraint (file size, API limits, time). EPISTEMIC AT SCALE: overall_truth/indeterminacy/falsity are aggregate confidence measures for the entire tensor. Computed from strand-level epistemic (mean or weighted average). SCHEMA VALIDATION: When Claude responds, the tool input MUST conform to PROJECTION_SCHEMA. If not, Anthropic API rejects the response. This ensures projector.py can safely deserialize without defensive validation. PARSING LOGIC: _parse_projection(raw: dict, cycle: int) converts schema-conforming dict into Tensor object. Creates Strand objects with tuple[KeyClaim], DeclaredLoss objects with LossCategory enum. IMMUTABILITY PRESERVED: All Tensor nested objects are tuples (immutable). _parse_projection creates frozen Tensor (via Pydantic ConfigDict frozen=True). TRACEABILITY: Schema includes descriptions for each field. Helps Claude understand what to emit. Also documents the contract for readers."
  },
  {
    "title": "Prompt Engineering: Cognitive Instructions for the Memory Controller",
    "content": "CYCLE 45 PROMPT DESIGN: _build_projection_prompt() is the cognitive instruction set for Claude (Haiku). PREAMBLE (lines 1-15 of prompt): Introduces role: 'You are a tensor projector — a memory controller.' Explains job: 'Take prior projected state + new content, produce UPDATED state.' CRITICAL DISTINCTION: 'This is not summarization. This is integration.' The projected state is like a running sum—previous values aren't listed, they're integrated into current value. Not appending, MERGING. RULES (enumerated): (1) Strands are thematic threads. Merge, split, create as content demands. (2) Key claims grounded in content. Assign honest T/I/F. (3) DECLARED LOSSES ARE CRITICAL. 'Silent loss is the enemy.' (4) Open questions carry forward unless resolved. (5) instructions_for_next is branch prediction. PRIOR TENSOR BLOCK: If prior_tensor exists, dumps full JSON via model_dump_json(indent=2). Preserves all strands, claims, losses, questions, instructions from prior cycle. Claude can see the complete prior state. NEW CONTENT BLOCK: Appends raw new_content parameter (conversation turns, user input, etc.). INVOCATION INSTRUCTION: 'Produce the updated tensor projection.' Signals Claude to use emit_tensor tool. DESIGN RATIONALE: The prompt is HONEST ENGINEERING. Doesn't hide complexity or constraints. Explicitly asks for losses to be declared. Emphasizes integration over summarization. This increases likelihood that Claude will produce coherent, traceable projections. TOKENS: The full prompt (prior tensor + new content + instructions) is typically 2000-4000 tokens for small-to-medium sessions. Haiku can handle 200K tokens, so headroom is abundant."
  },
