  },
  {
    "title": "Session State: Projector Maintains Durable Tensor Across Invocations",
    "content": "CYCLE 45 STATE MACHINE: Projector.__init__() initializes: _cycle = 0, _current_tensor = None, client (Anthropic), model (Haiku). MUTABLE SESSION STATE: _cycle and _current_tensor are mutable fields. They change across project() invocations. LIFECYCLE: (1) Create projector: p = Projector(). State: cycle=0, tensor=None. (2) First project(): p.project('content 1'). Increments cycle to 1. Produces tensor_1. Stores as _current_tensor. (3) Second project(): p.project('content 2'). Increments cycle to 2. Uses tensor_1 as prior. Produces tensor_2. Stores as _current_tensor. (4) Continue for n invocations. PROPERTIES: cycle (read-only int) returns _cycle. current_tensor (read-only Tensor|None) returns _current_tensor. Allows introspection without mutation. DESIGN INTENT: Single Projector instance can be used for an entire conversation session. Each project() call integrates new content into the accumulated tensor. This enables long-running cognitive sessions where memory is preserved across turns. ALTERNATIVE USAGE: Can also be stateless by passing prior tensor explicitly (not done in current design, but could be added). PERSISTENCE: Tensor is immutable (Pydantic frozen=True), so it can be safely serialized to JSON (via model_dump_json()) and persisted to disk or database. Can be reloaded and passed to a new Projector instance to resume session."
  },
